<h1>Interactive Rose Curve</h1>

<p>If you're not into Maths, just take the below as a pretty, interactive pattern. If you are, it's a <%= link_to "rose or rhodonea curve", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rose_(mathematics)" %>, ie: a curve described by the polar equation r = cos(kÎ¸). In my implementation, k is a rational number defined by a variable numerator and denominator.</p>

<canvas id="canvas-rose"></canvas>

<div>
  <label for="numerator">Numerator: </label>
  <input type="range" min="1" max="10" step="1" value="4" class="slider" id="numerator">
</div>
<div>
  <label for="denominator">Denominator: </label>
  <input type="range" min="1" max="10" step="1" value="1" class="slider" id="denominator">
</div>
<div>
  <label for="range">Proportion to draw: </label>
  <input type="range" min="0" max="360" step="1" value="360" class="slider" id="points-to-draw">
</div>
<div>
  <label for="step">Step</label>
  <input type="range" min="0.25" max="8" value="1" list="steps" class="slider" id="step">
  <datalist id="steps">
    <option value="0.25"></option>
    <option value="0.5"></option>
    <option value="1"></option>
    <option value="2"></option>
    <option value="4"></option>
    <option value="8"></option>
  </datalist>
</div>

<%= javascript_pack_tag 'projects/rose' %>
